Sentencas: Direct utilization of hydrocarbon and other renewable fuels is one of the most important issues concerning solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs).
Titulo: Doped CeO2-LaFeO3 Composite Oxide as an Active Anode for Direct Hydrocarbon-Type Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Mixed ionic and electronic conductors (MIECs) have been explored as anode materials for direct hydrocarbon-type SOFCs.
Titulo: Doped CeO2-LaFeO3 Composite Oxide as an Active Anode for Direct Hydrocarbon-Type Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: However, electrical conductivity of the most often reported MIEC oxide electrodes is still not-satisfactory.
Titulo: Doped CeO2-LaFeO3 Composite Oxide as an Active Anode for Direct Hydrocarbon-Type Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: As a result, mixed-conducting oxides with high electrical conductivity and catalytic activity are attracting considerable interest as an alternative anode material for noncoke depositing anodes.
Titulo: Doped CeO2-LaFeO3 Composite Oxide as an Active Anode for Direct Hydrocarbon-Type Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: In this study, we examine the oxide composite Ce(Mn,Fe)O-2-La(Sr)Fe(Mn)O-3 for use as an oxide anode in direct hydrocarbon-type SOFCs.
Titulo: Doped CeO2-LaFeO3 Composite Oxide as an Active Anode for Direct Hydrocarbon-Type Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: High performance was demonstrated for this composite oxide anode in direct hydrocarbon-type SOFCs, showing high maximum power density of approximately 1 W cm(-2) at 1073 K when propane and butane were used as fuel.
Titulo: Doped CeO2-LaFeO3 Composite Oxide as an Active Anode for Direct Hydrocarbon-Type Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The high power density of the cell results from the high electrical conductivity of the composite oxide in hydrocarbon and the high surface activity in relation to direct hydrocarbon oxidation.
Titulo: Doped CeO2-LaFeO3 Composite Oxide as an Active Anode for Direct Hydrocarbon-Type Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
